  "plan": "# Restaurant Booking System — Implementation Plan\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\nbackend/  (.NET 10 Web API)\nfrontend/ (React SPA + Vite + Tailwind + shadcn/ui)\n```\n\n- **Backend**: ASP.NET Core minimal API, in-memory persistence, Result-style domain errors, OpenAPI enabled via Swashbuckle.\n- **Frontend**: React 18, Vite, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui, TanStack Query, Orval-generated typed client from backend OpenAPI spec.\n\n---\n\n## Domain Model\n\n| Entity    | Fields |\n|-----------|--------|\n| Restaurant | Id, Name, Address, Tables[] |\n| Table     | Id, RestaurantId, Seats |\n| Booking   | Id, RestaurantId, TableId, CustomerName, PartySize, Date, TimeSlot (start, end), Status |\n\n**TimeSlot**: 1-hour blocks (e.g. 18:00–19:00). Party size must fit table seats.\n\n---\n\n## Vertical Slices\n\n### Slice 0 — Project scaffolding & in-memory store\n- `dotnet new webapi` with nullable, implicit usings, warnings-as-errors.\n- In-memory restaurant/table seed data.\n- Vite React project with Tailwind + shadcn/ui initialized.\n- Both projects build cleanly.\n\n### Slice 1 — List restaurants\n- **Backend**: `GET /api/restaurants` returns restaurant list with table info.\n- **Frontend**: Restaurant list page using shadcn Card components, TanStack Query.\n- **Orval**: Generate typed client from OpenAPI spec.\n\n### Slice 2 — List available time slots\n- **Backend**: `GET /api/restaurants/{id}/slots?date=YYYY-MM-DD&partySize=N`\n  - Returns available slots considering existing bookings and table capacity.\n  - Validates: unknown restaurant, invalid date (past), invalid party size (≤0).\n- **Frontend**: Slot picker UI, accessible and responsive.\n- **Tests**: Boundary tests for invalid date, invalid party size, unknown restaurant.\n\n### Slice 3 — Create booking\n- **Backend**: `POST /api/bookings`\n  - Body: restaurantId, customerName, partySize, date, timeSlot.\n  - Validates all fields, finds suitable table, checks for overlapping bookings.\n  - Returns booking confirmation or structured error.\n- **Frontend**: Booking form with validation, confirmation display.\n- **Tests**: Overlapping reservation boundary tests.\n\n### Slice 4 — List existing bookings\n- **Backend**: `GET /api/bookings?restaurantId=...` returns bookings.\n- **Frontend**: Bookings list with status indicators.\n\n### Slice 5 — Polish & verification\n- Run all backend checks: build, test, format.\n- Run all frontend checks: build, typecheck, lint, format:check, deadcode.\n- Verify Orval generation is reproducible.\n- README with run instructions.\n\n---\n\n## Backend Structure\n\n```\nbackend/\n  Program.cs              — minimal API endpoints + DI setup\n  Domain/\n    Restaurant.cs         — domain models\n    BookingResult.cs      — Result<T, Error> types\n    BookingService.cs     — pure domain functions\n  Infrastructure/\n    InMemoryStore.cs      — seeded in-memory persistence\n  RestaurantBooking.Tests/\n    BookingServiceTests.cs — boundary tests\n```\n\n---\n\n## Frontend Structure\n\n```\nfrontend/\n  src/\n    api/                  — Orval generated client + hooks\n    components/\n      ui/                 — shadcn/ui components\n      RestaurantList.tsx\n      BookingForm.tsx\n      BookingConfirmation.tsx\n      BookingList.tsx\n      TimeSlotPicker.tsx\n    App.tsx               — router + layout\n    main.tsx\n  orval.config.ts         — Orval config pointing at backend OpenAPI spec\n  tailwind.config.ts\n  vite.config.ts\n  package.json\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Decisions\n\n- **In-memory store**: seeded with 3 restaurants, each with 3–5 tables of varying capacity.\n- **Time slots**: fixed 1-hour blocks, lunch (12–14) and dinner (18–21).\n- **Orval**: fetch client with Zod validation, TanStack Query hooks.\n- **shadcn/ui**: Card, Button, Input, Select, Badge, Table, Dialog, Form components.\n- **Warnings as errors**: backend `<TreatWarningsAsErrors>true</TreatWarningsAsErrors>`.\n- **Formatting**: `dotnet format` for backend, `prettier --check` for frontend.\n\n---\n\n## Verification Checklist\n\n- [ ] `dotnet build` passes with warnings-as-errors\n- [ ] `dotnet test` passes (all boundary tests green)\n- [ ] `dotnet format --verify-no-changes` passes\n- [ ] `npm run build` passes\n- [ ] `npm run typecheck` passes\n- [ ] `npm run lint` passes\n- [ ] `npm run format:check` passes\n- [ ] `npm run deadcode` passes (via ts-prune or knip)\n- [ ] Orval client generation is reproducible\n- [ ] README has complete run instructions\n",
